[{"id":"VR652240","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal beam with 3 arrows of different lengths extending from 3 points on the beam as follows. Point A is at the left end of the beam. Arrow F sub 1 is the shortest arrow and it extends upward and to the left from point A at an angle of theta sub 1 from the vertical. Point B is at the center of the beam. Arrow F sub 2 is the longest arrow, and it extends downward and to the right from point B at an angle of theta sub 2 from the vertical. Point C is at the right end of the beam. Arrow F sub 3 is the median length arrow, and it extends upward and to the right from point C at an angle of theta sub 3 from the horizontal.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR652240.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three forces are exerted on a beam of negligible mass and length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span>. The locations, magnitudes, and directions of the forces are indicated in the figure. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> is at the center of the beam. Considering counterclockwise to be the direction of positive torque, which of the following is a correct expression for the net torque exerted on the rod about Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR652240_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 1 the cosine of theta sub 1, minus F sub 2 the cosine of th